body.description: The Maxell 190319 high-quality stereo headphones deliver an exceptional audio experience. With stunning stereo sound and exceptional bass. These headphones are lightweight and comfortable, with excellent noise isolation, and can be worn for long periods of time without discomfort. With a 3.5mm stereo jack and a 6ft cord, these headphones can easily reach your desktop or laptop computer, as well as other devices. Furthermore, the 3.5mm audio jack is robust and durable, making it compatible with nearly all smartphones, tablets, laptops, ipads, ipods, pcs, and other devices that use a single 3.5mm audio connection. These headphones are also portable and convenient, as they can be folded and carried in a small, soft pouch. These headphones are a must-have for anyone who enjoys listening to music and are ideal for use in school classrooms, libraries, spas, fitness centers, and other locations.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE THESE EAR PHONES
reviews.reviewText: They fit well, nice and flat, reasonably good sound considering low price. Liked them so much I bought an extra 2 sets. I use one set in my bedroom, one at my desk, and one spare, which could make a nice gift.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Replacement/Upgrade for Roku Ear Buds
reviews.reviewText: My wife is rather hard of hearing, and rather than deafen the rest of us when watching TV, she wears out her Roku headphones. Horrors, one earbud stopped working. As the alternative was somewhat loud in the house, I moved expeditiously to repair/replace the faulty unit. When she said she didn't like the earbuds anyway because they kept falling out, a light headphone set seemed indicated. We chose these, and she is very pleased with the upgrade. The sound is an better, the adjustable feature has yielded a better fit, they are more comfortable over her ears rather than in them, and they don't fall off. They are a simple plug in replacement for the earbuds. Best, Sounds of Silence have returned for the rest of us.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for Classroom Computers!
reviews.reviewText: I work in a middle school special needs classroom. We have 2 autistic boys in the room who spend their daily computer time watching movie clips from various children's movies and TV shows. They usually watch the same clip over and over and over. It gets really annoying and loud with 2 different soundtracks going on simultaneously. They were using ear buds when watching their clips, but those broke before the holidays. After a week of no headphones, I decided to order these for them. I actually ordered 3 pairs, one for each of our classroom computers. These aren't super high quality headphones, but they are working great for our students. Yes, it would be wonderful if we had some of those nice, padded, over the ear earphones, but we don't. Since these were purchased with my own money, this was what was in my budget. I'm not sure I would order these for myself, but for the students, they do the job!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars These are apparently for small children, nothing says than on the package though.
reviews.reviewText: The sound is decent. not too loud unless you crank it up, and no noticeable noise or distortion. The price is reasonable.They are not comfortable. much to small for adult heads, and the ends of the headband come out of the track and poke you in the ear or head. The foam pad would be adequate, if the size issue did not create a lot of force on the headphones, causing them to press pretty noticeably into your ears.probably good for kids or older people with small heads. I wear a size 7 hat, so mine is not large, cannot imagine anyone wearing a 7 1/4 or larger hat even getting these on at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My Grandson Loves These
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these headphones for my 4 1/2 grandson who has been diagnosed as having level 3 autism. He is vocal, but not verbal, and enjoys music very much. I got him a tablet to listen to music and it came with a cordless, over the ears headset which my grandson could absolutely not tolerate. I wanted to get him non restrictive, headphones to listen to his tablet quietly. I took a chance and purchased these. Things turned out well. They are lightweight, adjustable to accommodate his smaller size head and he can play with the cord contently, (which is part of his condition to have something between his fingers to manipulate repeatedly.) They resonate a clear crisp full stereo sound that apparently pleases my little one. I will say this has been a great buy.

No.But if you need a cheap option for listening to audio on your laptop etc without bothering others around you...Well this is the solution.You can actually turn up the volume, unlike a lot of blue tooth options.Blue tooth likes to keep the volume low to protect your hearing and keep them out of lawsuits.

reviews.reviewTitle: Good for low usage and low demand
reviews.reviewText: I got these an an add on because I just wanted some inexpensive headphones for listening to my pre-edit podcasts. Because they just sit on a hook on my desk when I’m not using them, my expectations for them are very low, which means that for the price and my anticipated use, they get five stars. Just be aware that if you want headphones to wear on the bus or out jogging, these are NOT those headphones. You’d go through a pair a month because the construction is a bit cheap. (And you’d probably rate them one star and leave an outraged review.) I got what I paid for and they work exactly as I need them to.
É um fone de ouvido simples, muito leve, fácil de carregar. Atende bem minhas necessidades.

As far as bargain priced headphones go these are really good. Great sound quality and feather weight design. Despite what some of the product notes say this is not a headset. There is no microphone and the cord is not retractable. These are really a good value.
